chunks.en: I see many people around me pronounce it as "Ningnius", I usually pronounce it as "Ningnakesi", and I just searched that linus also has a second pronunciation.
chunks.zh: 我看身边有不少人读 “宁牛斯"，我一般发音宁纳克丝，刚搜了一下 linus 也是发第二种音。

chunks.en: Local dialect pronunciation: リナックス (Li Na Ku Su)
chunks.zh: 家乡话读法： リナックス  （李那 库苏）

chunks.en: I didn't find that classic Zhihu answer, let me repeat it: "Linux is free, including its pronunciation"
chunks.zh: 没蹲到那个经典的知乎回答，那我来复述一下吧：「 Linux 是自由的，包括它的发音」

chunks.en: It feels like many people don't distinguish between n and l...
chunks.zh: 感觉 n ，l 不分的好多啊。。。

chunks.en: I was pronouncing it wrong before. I always pronounced it as "Linniu'kesi". It turns out to be "'Lei Ni ke si", with the stress on the first syllable. https://www.google.com/search?q=how+to+pronounce+linux
chunks.zh: 原来我以前都读错了。一直读  林牛'克斯。原来是 '累尼克斯，重音在前。https://www.google.com/search?q=how+to+pronounce+linux

chunks.en: Ni nin ke si or pronounce it one letter at a time
chunks.zh: 妮您可死或者一个字母一个字母的读出来

chunks.en: If you can't distinguish between l and n, what's the point of talking about it?
chunks.zh: l n 都不分，还说个啥
